Tomato jam is one of my favorite things to make in the summer when our garden is out of control and tomatoes are everywhere. It’s sweet, spicy, tangy, complex, and so special. Some of this jammy goodness added to your next charcuterie board? Unreal. I like to eat it on egg breakfast sandwiches, on a nice fancy piece of bread toasted with some soft cheese, along side some roast chicken, you name it. I also maybe have eaten it straight out of the jar, too. 😛😂

✨✨✨Tomato Jam✨✨✨
6 lbs fresh tomatoes, whole if cherry tomatoes, chopped and cored if larger 
4 c sugar
1/2 c bottled lime juice
1/2 tsp ground ginger 
2 to 4 tsp red pepper flakes, to taste
1 T salt
1 tsp cinnamon
1 tsp cumin

Combine everything in a large pot, stir to combine. Bring mixture to a boil over medium-high heat, stirring occasionally. Reduce heat to medium low to maintain a constant simmer, continuing to stir occasionally. 
Simmer jam for 2 to 2 1/2-ish hours, until it becomes thick, sticky, and jammy. You may now can the jam according to your favorite method to keep for later, or allow to cool fully and store in the fridge (or freezer!) to eat sooner. 

Note: ✨Spices may be adjusted to personal preference. ✨ Freshly ground black pepper can be substituted if you’re not a spicy guy. I make mine very spicy and even my 6 year old likes it as the sweetness balances everything out. ✨Overall yield will vary based on type of tomato and level of reduction your jam reaches, but mine is usually around 6 half pint jars. ✨Recipe can easily be halved, and will cook a bit faster at that point. ✨ Do not reduce amount citrus juice if canning jam. ✨Enjoy 😛🍅

(Ps like and save this video and I’ll share more recipes soon I promise) #tastesgreatduh #tomatojam #tomatogirl #tomatogirlsummer #homepreserving #recipe #summerproduce

✨an update on my mom:✨
Last summer, my mom @dawnbaby007 was diagnosed with stage three breast cancer and began her treatment journey very shortly after. It was a year of ups and downs and complications and challenges, but the outpouring of love and support from our community kept her going. 

Unfortunately, some routine follow-up testing showed the cancer is back, and very aggressive. My mom begins chemo in a couple weeks and will have surgery immediately following that. This is quite a shock to us all and honestly just fucking sucks. 

My mom has been a self-employed artist and hairstylist forever, and I’m so lucky to have been raised in such a creative inspiring environment that led me to being the person I am today. However, being a self employed artist means no traditional employer-supplied safety net of sick days and good insurance, no early retirement, no job security while you’re out sick for months on end. I want my son to grow up with my mom, his only grandparent, in his life. I want my mom to keep sharing her weird wild wonderful art (and self) with the world. The only way this can happen is if we all come together to help however we can. 

Donating to the link in my bio is amazing but truly anything helps. Resharing this post and link is so so so helpful and appreciated. If you’re a cool friend, my mom LOVES mail and would love a postcard or a drawing or a love note from you (hit me up for her address). If you’re in Eugene, be on the lookout for updates regarding help with meal trains and dog walks. If you’re so inclined, lighting a candle and sending some good vibes her way is very welcomed too. Truly anything helps, and my family is humbled by the support we have received. Thank you ✨💕

Wow! Santa brought me a salon for Christmas! Just kidding, but this is the surprise I’ve been hinting at! 
My friend @hairpotiondan found this space on Craigslist just a few short weeks ago and it’s been a whirlwind getting everything set up since then. Dan and I have worked together twice before and I’m so stoked to get to share this space with them! 
The holidays are the BUSIEST time of year for me and perhaps the single worst time to surprise open a business with little to no warning, but we’re doin the damn thing and it’s coming together nicely. 
I’ve spent all my free time the last 2 weeks driving all the heck over the state and surrounding areas to Eugene, Salem, Cottage Grove, Vancouver, Sherwood, etc fetching furniture off fb marketplace and thrift stores. 
I’ve been digging deep in my garage for all these gold mirrors I’ve been hoarding for a decade, and hitting up @dawnbaby007 ’s garage too for all her extra salon furniture since she closed up shop on her salon in 2020. @allihalla rewired and mounted this BONKERS antique chandelier and I’m forever indebted for her labor of love (shout out to @_siddlin for being the best volunteer lighting designer too!)
It’s been nonstop and I’m so thankful for everyone who has helped in anyway. If you wanna help out or buy me a little Christmas present, there is a wishlist linked in my stories. 
This is the only the beginning but I truly can’t wait to share more @wild.pansy.studios with y’all 🥲🥲🥲

Tomorrow is my first day at @wild.pansy.studios and I can’t even believe its finally happening! The amount of work and care that went into this place is abundant, and we’re just getting started, baby!
